LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1142
Introduced by Hardin, 48.
Read first time January 20, 2026
Committee: Government, Military and Veterans Affairs
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Nebraska Visitors Development Act; to
2 amend sections 53-501, 81-3701, 81-3702, 81-3703, 81-3706.01,
3 81-3710, 81-3711, 81-3711.01, 81-3712, 81-3713, 81-3714, 81-3721,
4 81-3726, 81-3728, 81-3729, and 81-3730, Reissue Revised Statutes of
5 Nebraska, section 77-3012, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
6 2024, and section 81-3725, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025; to
7 authorize the Department of Economic Development to administer the
8 act; to provide for a Director of Tourism; to change provisions
9 relating to the Nebraska Tourism Commission; to define a term; to
10 change the name of a fund; to harmonize provisions; to provide an
11 operative date; to repeal the original sections; and to declare an
12 emergency.
13 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 53-501, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 53-501 (1) The Nebraska Craft Brewery Board is created. All board
4 members shall be (a) citizens of Nebraska, (b) at least twenty-one years
5 of age, and (c) either engaged in or previously engaged in the
6 manufacture or the wholesale or retail sale of beer in this state or
7 engaged or previously engaged in the production in this state of
8 agricultural products that are utilized in the brewing process. The board
9 shall consist of seven members to be appointed by the Governor on a
10 nonpartisan basis. At least two board members shall be selected by the
11 Governor from a list of no fewer than ten candidates submitted by the
12 Nebraska Craft Brewers Guild or its successor organization. In addition,
13 at least two board members shall be selected by the Governor from a list
14 of no fewer than ten candidates submitted by the Associated Beverage
15 Distributors of Nebraska or its successor organization. The Director of
16 Agriculture or his or her designee and the Director of Tourism of the
17 Department of Economic Development executive director of the Nebraska
18 Tourism Commission or his or her designee shall be nonvoting, ex officio
19 members of the board.
20 (2) Whenever a vacancy occurs on the board for any reason, the
21 Governor shall appoint an individual to fill such vacancy pursuant to the
22 qualifications set forth in subsection (1) of this section.
23 Sec. 2. Section 77-3012, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
24 2024, is amended to read:
25 77-3012 (1) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (5) of this
26 section, a tax is hereby imposed and levied, in the amount and in
27 accordance with this section, upon the net operating revenue of all cash
28 devices operating within the State of Nebraska for profit or gain either
29 directly or indirectly received. The tax shall be paid in the amount and
30 manner specified in this section.
31 (2) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (5) of this section,
-2-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 beginning on and after July 1, 2025, any distributor of a cash device,
2 and any operator of a cash device if the operator is not subject to a
3 revenue-sharing or other agreement with a distributor who is paying the
4 tax, shall pay a tax for each cash device in operation each calendar
5 quarter during the taxable year. The tax shall be collected by the
6 department and due and payable on January 1, April 1, July 1, and October
7 1 of each year on each cash device in operation during the preceding
8 calendar quarter. For each cash device put into operation on a date
9 subsequent to a quarterly due date that has not been included in
10 computing the tax imposed and levied by the Mechanical Amusement Device
11 Tax Act, the tax shall be due and payable on the immediately succeeding
12 quarterly due date.
13 (3) The amount of the tax imposed and levied under this section
14 shall be five percent of the net operating revenue for each cash device.
15 The quarterly tax shall be submitted on a form prescribed by the Tax
16 Commissioner documenting the total gross and net operating revenue for
17 that quarter.
18 (4) The Tax Commissioner shall remit the taxes collected pursuant to
19 this section to the State Treasurer for credit as follows:
20 (a) Twenty percent to the Charitable Gaming Operations Fund for
21 enforcement of the act and maintenance of the central server;
22 (b) Two and one-half percent to the Compulsive Gamblers Assistance
23 Fund;
24 (c) Two and one-half percent to the General Fund;
25 (d) Ten percent to the Nebraska Tourism Commission Promotional Cash
26 Fund;
27 (e) Forty percent to the Property Tax Credit Cash Fund; and
28 (f) The remaining twenty-five percent to the county treasurer of the
29 county in which the cash device is located to be distributed as follows:
30 (i) If the cash device is located completely within an unincorporated
31 area of a county, the remaining twenty-five percent shall be distributed
-3-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 to the county in which the cash device is located, or (ii) if the cash
2 device is located within the limits of a city or village in such county,
3 one-half of the remaining twenty-five percent shall be distributed to
4 such county and one-half of the remaining twenty-five percent shall be
5 distributed to the city or village in which such cash device is located.
6 (5) This section does not apply to cash devices operated by a
7 fraternal benefit society organized and licensed under sections 44-1072
8 to 44-10,109 or a recognized veterans organization as defined in section
9 80-401.01.
10 Sec. 3. Section 81-3701, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
11 amended to read:
12 81-3701 Sections 81-3701 to 81-3730 and sections 6 and 8 of this act
13 shall be known and may be cited as the Nebraska Visitors Development Act.
14 Sec. 4. Section 81-3702, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
15 amended to read:
16 81-3702 The purposes of the Nebraska Visitors Development Act are
17 (1) to create the Nebraska Tourism Commission to promote Nebraska as a
18 tourism destination and to administer programs to attract an increasing
19 number of visitors to Nebraska and further the use of travel and tourism
20 facilities in Nebraska, (2) to provide for a lodging tax on hotels for
21 the purpose of establishing a State Visitors Promotion Cash Fund, and (3)
22 to authorize the governing body of any county to appoint a visitors
23 committee and impose a lodging tax on hotels for the purpose of
24 establishing a County Visitors Promotion Fund and a County Visitors
25 Improvement Fund.
26 Sec. 5. Section 81-3703, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
27 amended to read:
28 81-3703 For purposes of the Nebraska Visitors Development Act,
29 unless the context otherwise requires, the definitions found in sections
30 81-3704 to 81-3709.01 and section 6 of this act apply.
31 Sec. 6. Department means the Department of Economic Development.
-4-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 Sec. 7. Section 81-3706.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 81-3706.01 Highway tourism marker means a marker of a particular
4 style authorized by the department commission to designate tourism
5 attractions.
6 Sec. 8. (1) The department shall administer the Nebraska Visitors
7 Development Act and shall have the authority to:
8 (a) Employ personnel and contract for services as needed to carry
9 out the department's duties under the act;
10 (b) Procure and evaluate data and information necessary for the
11 proper administration of the act;
12 (c) Develop and approve state marketing campaigns;
13 (d) Develop and administer a program to provide promotional
14 services, technical assistance, and state aid to local governments and
15 the tourism industry;
16 (e) Cooperate with federal, state, and local governments and private
17 individuals and organizations to carry out any of the functions of the
18 department and purposes of the Nebraska Visitors Development Act; and
19 (f) Actively coordinate and develop working partnerships with other
20 state agencies, including, but not limited to, the Commission on Indian
21 Affairs, the Game and Parks Commission, the Nebraska Arts Council, the
22 Nebraska State Historical Society, and the University of Nebraska.
23 (2) The Director of Economic Development shall appoint a Director of
24 Tourism at a salary fixed by the Director of Economic Development. The
25 Director of Tourism shall serve at the pleasure of the Director of
26 Economic Development.
27 (3) The department may adopt and promulgate rules and regulations to
28 carry out the Nebraska Visitors Development Act.
29 Sec. 9. Section 81-3710, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
30 amended to read:
31 81-3710 (1) The Nebraska Tourism Commission is created. For
-5-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 administrative purposes, the commission shall be located and staffed
2 within the department.
3 (2) The members of the commission shall consist of the Director of
4 Economic Development and twelve residents of the State of Nebraska
5 appointed by the Governor, to include one member representing a state
6 chamber of commerce organized under the Nebraska Nonprofit Corporation
7 Act, and one member appointed from each of the eleven districts described
8 in subsection (3) (2) of this section. The members appointed by the
9 Governor shall be subject to approval by the majority of the members of
10 the Legislature. The term of the member representing a state chamber of
11 commerce shall be four years, and the terms of the district members shall
12 be as provided in subdivision (3)(b) (2)(b) of this section. No appointed
13 member may serve more than two successive terms. Four of the district
14 members shall have professional, volunteer, or public service experience
15 that contributes to the fiduciary and governance duties of the
16 commission. Seven of the district members shall be affiliated with the
17 tourism industry.
18 (3)(a) (2)(a) For purposes of this section, the state is hereby
19 divided into eleven districts. The limits and designations of the eleven
20 districts shall be as follows:
21 (i) District No. 1. Douglas County;
22 (ii) District No. 2. Lancaster County;
23 (iii) District No. 3. The counties of Richardson, Pawnee, Nemaha,
24 Johnson, Otoe, Gage, Saline, and Jefferson;
25 (iv) District No. 4. The counties of Cass and Sarpy;
26 (v) District No. 5. The counties of Saunders, Washington, Dodge,
27 Colfax, Stanton, Cuming, Burt, Thurston, Wayne, Cedar, Dixon, and Dakota;
28 (vi) District No. 6. The counties of Butler, Polk, Platte, Merrick,
29 Nance, Boone, Madison, Pierce, Antelope, Knox, Holt, and Boyd;
30 (vii) District No. 7. The counties of Thayer, Nuckolls, Webster,
31 Adams, Clay, Fillmore, Seward, York, Hamilton, Franklin, and Harlan;
-6-

