4 Sec. 11. Section 81-3711.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
5 is amended to read:
6 81-3711.01 (1) The department commission may mark significant
7 tourism attractions in Nebraska.
8 (2) The department commission may (a) determine what tourism
9 attractions are significant to the State of Nebraska, (b) expend funds
10 for the purchase of highway tourism markers, (c) designate the
11 approximate location of highway tourism markers, (d) preserve, replace,
12 or modify highway tourism markers, and (e) accept gifts and encourage
13 local participation in and contribution to the erection of highway
14 tourism markers through the use of gifts and matching-fund agreements.
15 Such funds shall be deposited into the State Visitors Promotion Cash
16 Fund. The department commission shall not expend funds for the purchase
17 of highway tourism markers until funding has been secured through gifts
18 or otherwise.
19 (3) The department commission may appoint and delegate to a special
20 committee the duties of research and investigation to assist in the
21 determination of tourism attractions that should be designated by highway
22 tourism markers. The Department of Transportation shall erect and
23 maintain highway tourism markers and shall determine the exact location
24 of highway tourism markers with consideration given for the safety and
25 welfare of the public.
26 (4) The department commission may secure payment to the state for
27 the actual replacement cost of any highway tourism markers damaged or
28 destroyed, accidentally or otherwise. Any funds so collected shall be
29 remitted to the State Treasurer for credit to the State Visitors
30 Promotion Cash Fund for the procurement of highway tourism markers.
31 (5) Nothing in this section shall be construed to restrict the
-9-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 placement of any marker or signage on private property.
2 Sec. 12. Section 81-3712, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
3 amended to read:
4 81-3712 For purposes of transition, employees of the commission
5 Travel and Tourism Division of the Department of Economic Development
6 shall be considered employees of the department commission and shall
7 retain their rights under the state personnel system or pertinent
8 bargaining agreement, and their service shall be deemed continuous. This
9 section does not grant employees any new rights or benefits not otherwise
10 provided by law or bargaining agreement or preclude the department
11 commission from exercising any of the prerogatives of management set
12 forth in section 81-1311 or as otherwise provided by law. This section is
13 not an amendment to or substitute for the provisions of any existing
14 bargaining agreements.
15 Sec. 13. Section 81-3713, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
16 amended to read:
17 81-3713 The department commission shall develop a statewide
18 strategic plan to cultivate and promote tourism in Nebraska. The
19 department commission shall review the plan annually and update as
20 necessary. The plan shall include:
21 (1) A review of revenue in the State Visitors Promotion Cash Fund
22 available for tourism development at the state level;
23 (2) An examination of best management practices for the tourism
24 industry;
25 (3) Marketing strategies for promoting tourism;
26 (4) Methods to expand existing tourism capacity which may include
27 encouraging regional cooperation, collaboration, or privatization; and
28 (5) Recommended strategies to provide technical assistance,
29 marketing services, and state aid to local governments and the tourism
30 industry in Nebraska.
31 Sec. 14. Section 81-3714, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
-10-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 amended to read:
2 81-3714 The State Visitors Promotion Cash Fund is created. The fund
3 shall be administered by the department commission. The fund shall
4 consist of revenue deposited into the fund pursuant to section 81-3715
5 and money donated as gifts, bequests, or other contributions from public
6 or private entities. Funds made available by any department or agency of
7 the United States may also be credited to the fund if so directed by such
8 department or agency. The department commission shall use the proceeds of
9 the fund to generally promote and market the State of Nebraska, to
10 encourage, and attract visitors to and within the State of Nebraska, to
11 erect and replace highway tourism markers, to enhance the use of travel
12 and tourism facilities within the state, and to provide grants to
13 communities and organizations , and to contract with the Department of
14 Administrative Services to provide support services to the commission,
15 including, but not limited to, accounting and personnel functions. The
16 proceeds of the fund shall be in addition to funds appropriated to the
17 department commission from the General Fund. Transfers may be made from
18 the State Visitors Promotion Cash Fund to the General Fund at the
19 direction of the Legislature. The State Treasurer shall transfer one
20 million dollars from the State Visitors Promotion Cash Fund to the
21 General Fund on or before June 30, 2019, on such dates and in such
22 amounts as directed by the budget administrator of the budget division of
23 the Department of Administrative Services. Any money in the State
24 Visitors Promotion Cash Fund available for investment shall be invested
25 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
26 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act. Beginning
27 October 1, 2024, any investment earnings from investment of money in the
28 fund shall be credited to the General Fund.
29 Sec. 15. Section 81-3721, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
30 amended to read:
31 81-3721 All contracts awarded by the department commission shall be
-11-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 subject to the State Procurement Act. The department commission shall
2 comply with the rules, regulations, procedures, and guidelines
3 established by the Department of Administrative Services for contracts.
4 Sec. 16. Section 81-3725, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
5 amended to read:
6 81-3725 (1) The department commission shall develop a program to
7 provide marketing assistance grants to communities and organizations
8 hosting national or international-caliber events held in Nebraska that
9 have the potential to attract a significant percentage of out-of-state
10 visitors and to generate favorable national or international press
11 coverage for Nebraska.
12 (2) A community or organization applying for a marketing assistance
13 grant shall provide a plan to the department commission that includes:
14 (a) Documentation that the event will attract out-of-state visitors; (b)
15 details regarding the type of marketing that would be carried out with
16 state funds; (c) methodologies used to track the impact of marketing
17 efforts and the number of out-of-state visitors attending the event; and
18 (d) details regarding the potential national or international press
19 coverage that will be generated by the event.
20 (3)(a) The department commission shall develop a program to provide
21 innovative tourism grants to communities or organizations that provide
22 tourism and visitor promotion services, host events, or promote
23 attractions that result in either (i) an increased number of nonlocal,
24 instate visitors or (ii) an increased number of both nonlocal, instate
25 visitors and out-of-state visitors. Innovative tourism grants may
26 include, but not be limited to, marketing assistance, planning
27 assistance, basic support, and regional cooperation. Innovative tourism
28 grants shall not be used for equipment or capital facility development or
29 improvements.
30 (b) When awarding innovative tourism grants under the program, the
31 department commission shall award up to five hundred thousand dollars in
-12-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 innovative tourism grants to any such city or village each fiscal year.
2 (4) The Director of Tourism executive director shall convene a
3 technical review committee of no fewer than three individuals
4 representing the public sector, the private sector, and citizens at
5 large. The technical review committee, the Director of Tourism, and the
6 Director of Economic Development and the executive director shall review
7 and score applications for marketing assistance grants and innovative
8 tourism grants and forward recommendations to the department commission
9 for approval by the department commission or a subcommittee of the
10 commission.
11 (5) Communities and organizations receiving marketing assistance
12 grants or innovative tourism grants authorized under this section shall
13 provide a final report to the department commission within ninety days
14 after the completion date of the event that includes event attendance,
15 the use of funds, and marketing impact information.
16 (6) The department commission shall adopt and promulgate rules and
17 regulations governing the grant programs authorized under this section.
18 Sec. 17. Section 81-3726, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
19 amended to read:
20 81-3726 The Tourism Conference Cash Fund is created. The fund shall
21 be administered by the department commission. All sums of money received
22 from fees from any conference or event held by the department commission
23 shall be deposited in the fund. The department commission shall use the
24 fund to defray expenses related to any conference or event sponsored by
25 the department commission. Any money in the fund available for investment
26 shall be invested by the state investment officer pursuant to the
27 Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment
28 Act.
29 Sec. 18. Section 81-3728, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
30 amended to read:
31 81-3728 (1) Vendors under contract with the department commission to
-13-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 develop, print, and distribute publications and promotional materials or
2 produce, sell, and distribute tourism promotional products on behalf of
3 the department commission shall, on a monthly basis, submit to the
4 department commission all revenue received from the sale of advertising
5 space in such publications or from the sale of such tourism promotional
6 products. Monthly submissions shall include an itemization of the sources
7 of revenue in a format as designated by the department commission.
8 Revenue from such sales shall be remitted to the State Treasurer for
9 credit to the Nebraska Tourism Commission Promotional Cash Fund.
10 (2) The department commission may enter into agreements directly
11 with retailers to sell tourism promotional products. If a retailer pays
12 for such products in full at the time of acquisition, the retailer shall
13 have no further reporting requirements. The department commission shall
14 remit payments received from retailers acquiring such products to the
15 State Treasurer for credit to the Nebraska Tourism Commission Promotional
16 Cash Fund.
17 Sec. 19. Section 81-3729, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
18 amended to read:
19 81-3729 The Nebraska Tourism Commission Promotional Cash Fund is
20 hereby created. The fund shall consist of revenue submitted by vendors
21 and retailers under section 81-3728 and revenue from the tax collected on
22 the net operating revenue of cash devices pursuant to section 77-3012.
23 Revenue from the sale of advertising shall be remitted to the State
24 Treasurer for credit to the fund. The department commission shall use the
25 fund to carry out its purposes under the Nebraska Visitors Development
26 Act. Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested by
27 the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion
28 Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
29 Sec. 20. Section 81-3730, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
30 amended to read:
31 81-3730 The department commission is authorized to develop and make
-14-

LB1142 LB1142
2026 2026
1 available for sale directly to the public tourism promotional products
2 related to state marketing campaigns developed and approved by the
3 department commission. The department commission may contract with
4 private vendors to produce, sell, and distribute such tourism promotional
5 products or enter into agreements directly with retailers as provided in
6 section 81-3728. Any revenue from the sale of such tourism promotional
7 products shall be credited to the Nebraska Tourism Commission Promotional
8 Cash Fund as provided in section 81-3728.
9 Sec. 21. This act becomes operative on July 1, 2026.
10 Sec. 22. Original sections 53-501, 81-3701, 81-3702, 81-3703,
11 81-3706.01, 81-3710, 81-3711, 81-3711.01, 81-3712, 81-3713, 81-3714,
